CREATE USER [name@domain.com] FROM EXTERNAL PROVIDER;
ALTER ROLE db_datareader ADD MEMBER [name@domain.com]; 

if it is security group then add the alias name

CREATE USER [Azure-ADGROUPNAME] FROM EXTERNAL PROVIDER;
ALTER ROLE db_datareader ADD MEMBER [Azure-ADGROUPNAME]


https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/sql-database/sql-database-manage-logins


FOR Managed instance

https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/sql-database/sql-database-managed-instance-aad-security-tutorial

USE master
GO
CREATE LOGIN [name@domain.com] FROM EXTERNAL PROVIDER
GO
